@* Root component. Rendered directly into #app by Program.cs.

   There is no <Router> on purpose: this app has exactly one screen, so routing
   would be dead weight the trimmer keeps only because we asked for it. A single
   root component is the natural minimal Blazor app here, and it keeps the
   comparison against Filament honest (neither side ships a router).

   The markup below is the SHARED DOM CONTRACT and must not be altered. *@

<h1 id="title">Counter</h1>

<p>Current count: <span id="counter-value">@currentCount</span></p>

<button id="increment" @onclick="Increment">Click me</button>

@code {
    private int currentCount = 0;

    private void Increment()
    {
        currentCount++;
    }
}
